  "text": "Indirana chiravasi differs from I. beddomii in having smaller finger 2 length (7.0-7.9 % SUL vs. 8.3-10.5 % SUL), webbing formula I1-2II1-3III1¼-3IV3-1¼V in male and I1-2II1-2½III1¼-3IV3-1¼V in female (vs. webbing formula, I1-2II1-2III1-3IV3-1V, in both males and females) and long, thin, shovel-shaped inner metatarsal tubercle (vs. long and stout inner metatarsal tubercle). Genetic difference between I. chiravasi and I. beddomii cannot be determined as [CITATION_1] have considered several genetically distinct populations as members of I. beddomii species complex.",
